The paper deals with the design and analysis of a quantization algorithm based on belief propagation, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm uses a low-density generator-matrix (LDGM) code, which is a type of error-correcting code commonly used in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses optimization of the degree distribution of the LDGM code, which is a common topic in statistical inference (cs.SI). The algorithm is applied to quantization of R^n, which is a common problem in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses simulation results comparing the proposed algorithm to trellis-coded quantization (TCQ), which is a common technique in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.LG).
